                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12565129" author="stack" created="Sun, 3 Feb 2008 00:17:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Add NCSA (apache-style logging), add being able to set log level and get a stack trace, add being able to set max jetty threads, and add some DEBUG-level logging to HConnectionManager around the cache so can get info for solving &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4&quot; title=&quot;hbase client makes too many requests against .META.,,1 table: caching of .META.,,1 lookups is broken?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12565479" author="bryanduxbury" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2008 19:14:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You&apos;re using a single REST server to serve 400 clients? That&apos;s really not ideal. You may be able to increase random read performance a little with caching, but I think you&apos;d be taking a pretty noticeable hit by aggregating your entire cluster&apos;s traffic through a single machine. Can you try the job with a larger number of REST servers? Like one per worker  host? That&apos;s how we do it at Rapleaf.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12565597" author="bien" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2008 23:17:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bryan,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am experimenting with different topologies.  The distribution of our random reads is extremely skewed, so I set up a single proxy cache (varnishd) for all our traffic.  This works much better than past experiments with smaller separate caches on individual work nodes.  The single proxy cache has scaled to our needs, despite living in a single process, so the traffic is already aggregated by the time the cache misses go to the rest server.  So, I&apos;d like to have a single rest server serving as the backend.  If this isn&apos;t possible, I&apos;m willing to expand the number of rest servers, but in that case it is not the traffic aggregation that is limiting our scaling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12565600" author="bryanduxbury" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2008 23:25:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, I understand. There&apos;s nothing complicated to adding more threads. At one point I had an option on the command line to do that, but ended up reverting it because 256 seemed like a lot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12566251" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2008 18:21:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that adds --max-num-threads= command line parameter. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12566253" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2008 18:26:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wasn&apos;t paying attention, saw that there&apos;s another patch from Stack already. However, that patch has a lot of contamination from other issues, at least one of which has been resolved with no need for a fix. Should we remove some of the excess in Stacks&apos;s patch, or use mine, or what?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12566260" author="stack" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2008 18:35:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shall we put the patches together?  All the stuff added by my patch is useful beyond &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4&quot; title=&quot;hbase client makes too many requests against .META.,,1 table: caching of .META.,,1 lookups is broken?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Being able to set log level in REST server, get thread dumps, apache-style logging).  I can do it if you want.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12566263" author="stack" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2008 18:43:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After chatting on IRC, we&apos;ll go w/ the targetted patch and open another issue to add logging, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 on 3.patch after review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12567151" author="bryanduxbury" created="Fri, 8 Feb 2008 18:32:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since patch has received +1 from Stack, I think we should commit the 3.patch version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12567167" author="stack" created="Fri, 8 Feb 2008 19:12:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed 3.patch.  Thanks Bryan.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
